<HEADLINE>
<P>
ELAINE J. SHEVCHENKO, 50; WIFE OF SOVIET DEFECTOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Elaine Jackson Shevchenko, 50, the wife and writing collaborator of a prominent 
Soviet defector, has died. 
</P>
<P>
She died in Washington on March 20 of cancer. 
</P>
<P>
She married Arkady Shevchenko in 1978, shortly after he quit his job as 
undersecretary general of the United Nations. 
</P>
<P>
Mrs. Shevchenko helped her husband write the book, "Breaking With Moscow." 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Obituary; Wire 
</P>
