<P>
FLEISCHMAN ON ABORTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The logic of Fleischman's point of view is irrefutable. It is refreshing to 
read an analysis that removes the advocacy component of the abortion 
discussion. 
</P>
<P>
Unfortunately, this perspective does not sway legislatures to pass 
anti-abortion laws, nor masses to march for choice. We are stuck with 
emotionalism, illogic, polarization and, I fear, no resolution or compromise. 
</P>
<P>
Abortion has become the central, hysterical issue in many American communities. 
Rather, the debate should be conducted within the context of other tough 
choices of life and death with which society must deal. 
