</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NASA managers recommended that the space shuttle Discovery take off on schedule 
from the Kennedy Space Center in Florida April 12 to launch the Hubble Space 
Telescope. 
</P>
<P>
Technicians found that a nut on the landing gear of another shuttle had moved 
out of alignment. NASA spokesman Ed Campion said analysis indicated the 
misaligned nut, likely caused by impact upon landing, posed no danger. A final 
decision on the launch is expected this week. 
</P>
