<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: MEXICAN FRUIT FLY FIND SPURS ROUND OF 
TRAPPING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
State agriculture officials announced Monday the discovery of a single Mexican 
fruit fly in East Los Angeles, triggering a round of intensive trapping in the 
area. 
</P>
<P>
The fly, which was found Friday in an orange tree, threatens many of the same 
fruits as the Mediterranean fruit fly. Officials said there are no plans now to 
conduct aerial malathion sprayings because only a single fly was found. The 
Medfly infestation in Los Angeles and Orange counties now covers about 500 
square miles and is the largest in Southern California's history. 
</P>
</TEXT>
