<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: LANDLORD SUES ACTRESS CORNELIA GUEST OVER 
RENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
New York socialite and aspiring actress Cornelia Guest was sued Monday for 
allegedly not paying the rent on her $5,000-per-month Beverly Hills home. 
</P>
<P>
The lawsuit, filed in Superior Court by Guest's landlord, Marlene Morris, 
contends Guest failed to pay rent that was due March 1. Guest rented the house 
on Hutton Drive in May, 1989. In her suit, Morris is seeking to evict Guest and 
receive $25,000 in damages at the rate of $166.67 per day plus punitive 
damages. 
</P>
<P>
Guest, whose renown is based in part on her being "Deb of the Year" of New York 
and a past romantic link to actor Sylvester Stallone, could not be reached for 
comment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
