<SECTION>
<P>
Metro; Part B; Page 2; Column 1 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
78 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: COUNTYWIDE; 
</P>
<P>
STRANDED FISHING BOAT TOWED TO SAFETY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The U.S. Coast Guard rescued three people in a fishing vessel early Monday 
after a propeller shaft broke down, leaving the boat disabled half a mile west 
of Santa Cruz Island. 
</P>
<P>
None of the three people aboard the Down Under was injured, said Petty Officer 
Robert Beals. 
</P>
<P>
The Coast Guard learned that the boat was disabled at 6 p.m. Sunday. A cutter 
was dispatched and it towed the boat through the night, reaching Santa Barbara 
at 5 a.m. Monday, Beals said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
