SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST : SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A prisoner accused of beating a court bailiff was ordered Monday to stand trial 
on attempted murder and assault charges. 
</P>
<P>
Chris Spells, who is also known as Ricky, is accused of beating Deputy Marshal 
Greg Giddings on March 6, after Giddings brought Spells back from a Superior 
Courtroom to a holding tank in the courthouse. 
</P>
<P>
Giddings, who has worked for the marshal's office 1 1/2 years, was knocked 
unconscious in the fight. 
</P>
<P>
The incident followed Spells' conviction by a jury trial of assault with a 
deadly weapon. 
</P>
<P>
Judge Richard Hanscom ordered Spells to appear in Superior Court on April 5 for 
scheduling of a trial date and arraignment on the new charges. 
</P>
