<P>
NORTH STARS BEAT TORONTO, CLOSE IN ON PLAYOFF BERTH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BLOOMINGTON, Minn. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Gaetan Duchesne ignited a four-goal first-period and the Minnesota North Stars 
held off the Toronto, 5-4, Monday night to move within one point of a playoff 
berth. 
</P>
<P>
The victory gives the North Stars a five-point lead over the Detroit Red Wings 
for the final playoff spot in the Norris Division. Each team has three games 
left. 
</P>
<P>
Brian Bellows' 53rd goal extended his goal-scoring streak to a club-record 
eight games. 
</P>
<P>
It may have been the North Stars' final regular-season game in the Met Center. 
Owners George and Gordon Gund have applied to move the team to the San 
Francisco Bay Area next season. 
</P>
