<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL BASEBALL; 
</P>
<P>
MONTE VISTA, STONE HAND GROSSMONT FIRST DEFEAT OF YEAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Robby Stone allowed just four hits to previously undefeated Grossmont (11-1) as 
Monte Vista High defeated the Foothillers, 4-2, Monday in a nonleague game at 
Monte Vista. 
</P>
<P>
Stone, a 6-foot-6 junior, had seven strikeouts to improve to 3-1. 
</P>
<P>
In the third inning for Monte Vista (9-3), catcher Vern Mullis (three for four) 
singled in Steve Ryan with Ernie Reyes scoring on an ensuing overthrow. Mullis 
scored on Darren Rucker's single. 
</P>
<P>
Santana 7, Helix 2 -- Santana's Ferdie Hollis (2-0) had a three-hit shutout 
going before allowing two runs in the seventh inning at Helix. Santana remained 
undefeated at 10-0. El Capitan 11, West Hills 1 -- El Capitan's Jim Marchesi 
was three for five with two doubles and two runs, and Greg Ransweiler (1-1) 
scattered four hits and struck out nine in six innings. 
</P>
<P>
El Cajon Valley 3, Mt. Miguel 0 -- John Hayward pitched a two-hit shutout at El 
Cajon. 
</P>
<P>
Valhalla 3, Granite Hills 3 -- Valhalla scored a run in the top of the seventh 
to tie Granite Hills. The game was called because of darkness after seven 
innings. 
</P>
