<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Times Mirror Buys Stake in Publisher: Times Mirror Co., which owns The Times 
and other media properties, said it has purchased about 45% of the stock of B. 
C. Decker Inc., a publisher of medical books and journals with offices in 
Toronto and Philadelphia. The price was not disclosed. Mosby-Year Book Inc., a 
Times Mirror subsidiary that also publishes medical books and journals, will 
continue to distribute Decker books in the United States and Canada. 
</P>
