<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL ROUNDUP: PLAN TO MAKE RECYCLED EGG CARTONS OKD BY U.S. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dolco Packaging Corp., a maker of food packaging products, said it became the 
first company to get federal approval to make egg cartons from recycled 
polystyrene packaging. 
</P>
<P>
The approval from the Food and Drug Administration is "a significant 
development in plastic recycling efforts," said Dolco, a unit of Olson 
Industries Inc. in Sherman Oaks. 
</P>
<P>
Dolco, which is reorganizing under federal bankruptcy laws, said it will be 
allowed to make egg cartons from recycled meat trays, fast-food containers, 
school lunch trays and beverage cups made from polystyrene. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
