<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL ROUNDUP: CRESCOTT SELLS SOME SHARES IN DATAPRODUCTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Crescott Partners, a New York investor group that abandoned a takeover bid for 
Dataproducts Corp. in January, cut its stake in the Woodland Hills 
computer-printer maker. 
</P>
<P>
In a filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission, Crescott said it sold 
411,911 common shares of Dataproducts between Jan. 24 and March 15 at prices 
between $5.87 and $10 a share. The group now owns 1.1 million shares. 
</P>
<P>
The sale included 334,772 shares sold back to Dataproducts for $10 a share 
under the company's self-tender offer, in which Dataproducts repurchased about 
20% of its stock as part of a restructuring plan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
