<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The chairman of a Senate panel on military construction said Monday that a Bush 
Administration request for $1.1 billion to renovate the Pentagon is "out of the 
question." 
</P>
<P>
Sen. Jim Sasser (D-Tenn.) acknowledged that the 47-year-old building is in need 
of repair but said the Administration's call for $1.1 billion over seven years 
would be difficult to heed in a time of shrinking budgets. 
</P>
<P>
"The military construction bill is going to get smaller, not larger," Sasser 
told Pentagon officials. 
