<P>
47 DIE IN DHAKA FERRY SINKING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
DHAKA, Bangladesh 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A crowded ferry boat capsized when passengers scrambled to save a child who 
fell overboard, and at least 47 people drowned, news reports said today. 
Fifty-six others were missing. 
</P>
<P>
The privately owned boat was carrying 153 people back from Myanmar (formerly 
Burma) after a day's trip when it sank Monday during high tide in the Naff 
River in southern Bangladesh, the United News of Bangladesh reported. 
</P>
<P>
The news agency quoted survivors as saying the ferry swayed and sank after 
passengers hurried to rescue a child who fell into the river from the boat. The 
child was among the dead. 
</P>
<P>
Among the dead were 24 women and five children. 
</P>
<P>
The news agency quoted local officials as saying the final death toll will be 
higher because many of the missing are presumed dead. 
</P>
