<P>
JEWELED EASTER EGG FOR SALE: $11.3 MILLION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LONDON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jewelers Kutchinsky, whose audacious creations are de rigueur in some jet set 
circles, said today they have crafted the ultimate Easter egg. 
</P>
<P>
The two-foot-high egg, made from 37 pounds of gold and studded with 20,000 pink 
diamonds, will go on sale for $11.3 million. 
</P>
<P>
"So far as we know, it is the biggest decorative egg of its kind in the world 
and contains the largest single collection of rare pink diamonds in any one 
piece," said designer Paul Kutchinsky. 
</P>
<P>
The egg opens electronically to reveal a miniature library with cabinets and 
books. A carousel then revolves to display a tiny portrait gallery where the 
eventual owners could feature their family. 
</P>
<P>
The egg will be unveiled on April 11, just before Easter, in London before 
being shown in Tokyo and New York. 
</P>
