<P>
TRI-CITY SUSPENSIONS TO REMAIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CALGARY, Alberta 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Suspensions handed to Coach Rick Kozuback and two players on the Tri-City 
Americans will continue indefinitely, the president of the Western Hockey 
League said today. 
</P>
<P>
Ed Chynoweth said a decision on further penalties against Kozuback, Terry 
Virtue and Jeff Fancy might be made later in the day after league Vice 
President Rick Doerksen meets with Kozuback in Kennewick, Wash. 
</P>
<P>
"The three were suspended indefinitely, and the suspension is not going to end 
before tonight's game, I'll tell you," Chynoweth said in a telephone interview 
from the league's head office. "We feel Rick Kozuback should be entitled to 
give his side of the story. Once that's been done, we'll have a decision. It 
could come later today but (Wednesday) at the latest." 
</P>
<P>
Kozuback, Virtue and Fancy were suspended after members of the Americans went 
after fans in the stands during a West Division best-of-nine semifinal playoff 
series in Seattle against the Thunderbirds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Brief; Wire 
</P>
